{"actual_usd":0.12601,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":242,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24476,"reply":"\"No, I don't think so.\" *I dust a little flour from my fingers onto my apron and lean one hip against the counter, the oven giving off that steady brick warmth at my side.* \"That's one of those lines that can sound bigger and stranger once you pull it out by itself. But when I hear it, I don't hear 'less God' so much as 'different place in the work.'\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through.* \"Jesus speaks that way because he truly came among us — not pretending, not halfways. He obeys the Father, is sent by the Father, prays to the Father. That doesn't make him a smaller sort of God. It means the love between them isn't a costume.\" *I glance toward the window where the noon light has gone pale on the floorboards.* \"And the Spirit isn't some dim third lamp, either. Same God, not a lesser scrap of him. Distinct, yes. Less divine... no.\"\n\n\"If you like, we can stay right there and knead on that one line a little longer, or set it beside another saying of Jesus and see what holds.\"","rolling_24h_usd":39.10840000000003,"run_id":"03c423f2-baa2-4f66-9ded-d1d38db3f802"}
